--- about.html ---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About – HealthGuide AI</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Learn what HealthGuide AI is, how it works, and what it is (and is not) designed to do.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://YOURUSERNAME.github.io/about.html">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  <script defer src="script.js"></script>
</head>
<body data-page="about">
<header class="site-header">
  <div class="container header-inner">
    <a href="index.html" class="logo">HealthGuide<span>AI</span></a>
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="index.html" class="nav-link">Home</a>
      <a href="about.html" class="nav-link">About</a>
      <a href="privacy.html" class="nav-link">Privacy</a>
      <button class="nav-button" id="openAuth">Login / Premium</button>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="container page-main">
  <h1>About HealthGuide AI</h1>
  <p>
    HealthGuide AI is an educational web app designed to help you make sense of symptoms in plain language.
    It is not a diagnostic tool. Instead, it gives you structured information, common everyday causes,
    general red flags, and suggestions about what type of doctor might be able to help.
  </p>
  <p>
    The goal is to support your conversations with real healthcare professionals, not to replace them.
    We want you to feel more prepared, more informed, and less overwhelmed when you talk about your health.
  </p>
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>
    Each symptom guide is written in simple language and follows the same structure. You can browse popular topics
    or use the search box on the home page to find something specific.
  </p>
  <h2>Premium features</h2>
  <p>
    Premium tools (journal, questions to ask your doctor, and summaries) are shown in this demo using local
    storage only. In a full version, these would be connected to secure accounts and checkout.
  </p>

  <div class="disclaimer-box">
    HealthGuide AI is for general education only and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
    For individual medical questions, please contact a qualified healthcare professional.
  </div>
</main>

